  "prompt": "I have a dandruff problem. I wash my hair every other day, which makes my hair dry. If not washed, my scalp becomes oily, and dandruff and hair loss increase. What should I do?",
  "response": "Here are some recommendations to help manage your dandruff and hair health:\n\n1. Shampoo selection\n- Use an anti-dandruff shampoo with ingredients like:\n- Zinc pyrithione\n- Ketoconazole\n- Selenium sulfide\n- Salicylic acid\n\n2. Washing frequency\n- Try washing every 2-3 days instead of daily\n- Use lukewarm water, not hot\n- Gently massage scalp while washing\n\n3. Hydration and conditioning\n- Use a moisturizing conditioner\n- Apply conditioner mainly to hair ends, not scalp\n- Consider leave-in conditioners\n\n4. Natural remedies\n- Tea tree oil\n- Apple cider vinegar rinse\n- Coconut oil treatment\n- Aloe vera\n\n5. Lifestyle factors\n- Reduce stress\n- Eat a balanced diet\n- Stay hydrated\n- Get enough sleep\n\n6. Additional tips\n- Use a soft brush\n- Avoid tight hairstyles\n- Limit heat styling\n- Consider using a humidifier\n\n7. If problems persist\n- Consult a dermatologist\n- They might prescribe medicated shampoos or treatments\n\nRemember, finding the right solution may take time and experimentation.",
